# Email Verification Flow — FROZEN

This flow was intentionally designed and QA-tested. **Do not modify any part of it without the explicit written approval of the project owner.**

## Architecture: JWT issued only after email verification

```
Register → no JWT → "Check your inbox" screen
     ↓
Click link in email → POST /auth/verify-email → returns JWT
     ↓
saveToken(jwt) → router.replace("/dashboard") → dashboard opens
```

Unverified users have **no JWT** → they cannot reach any `(app)` route → middleware redirects to `/login`.

## What is frozen and why

| File | What to preserve |
|------|-----------------|
| `backend/auth/routes.py` — `register()` | Returns `RegisterResponse` (user only, **no JWT**). JWT is issued by `verify_email()` only. |
| `backend/auth/routes.py` — `login()` | Raises HTTP 403 "Email not verified. Please check your inbox." if `user.is_verified` is False. Token is **never** issued to unverified users. |
| `backend/auth/routes.py` — `verify_email()` | Returns `VerifyEmailResponse` with JWT token after marking user verified. |
| `backend/auth/schemas.py` | `RegisterResponse` has no token field. `VerifyEmailResponse` has token/expires_in/user. Do not merge them back. |
| `frontend/app/(auth)/signup/page.tsx` | No `saveToken()` after register. No "Go to sign in" link. Has **"← Back"** button that resets `verificationSent` state. |
| `frontend/app/(auth)/login/page.tsx` | Reads `?error=email_not_verified` query param and shows amber banner. The 403 from `/login` also surfaces as a form error. |
| `frontend/app/(auth)/verify/page.tsx` | On success: `saveToken(data.token)` from verify response, then `router.replace("/dashboard")`. No conditional checks needed. |
| `frontend/app/(app)/dashboard/page.tsx` | On "email not verified" error from `/clients/me`: set `redirecting=true`, call `removeToken()`, then `router.replace("/login?error=email_not_verified")`. Show loading spinner during redirect. |
| `frontend/middleware.ts` | All `(app)` routes are in `PROTECTED_PATHS`. Cookie check redirects unauthenticated users to `/login`. |
| `backend/auth/service.py` — `reset_password()` | `user.is_verified = True` on password reset is **intentional** (email link proves ownership). Do not remove. |

## Invariants (must always hold)

1. `POST /auth/register` **never** returns a JWT token.
2. `POST /auth/login` **raises 403** if the user's email is not verified.
3. `POST /auth/verify-email` **always** returns a JWT token on success.
4. An unauthenticated user who navigates to any `(app)` route is redirected to `/login` by middleware.
5. Clicking the verification link from email saves the token and redirects to `/dashboard` — no intermediate `/login`.
6. Resetting password via email link automatically verifies the account (`is_verified = True`).
7. `EmailVerificationGuard` component does not exist — do not re-create it.
8. The "Check your inbox" screen has a **"← Back"** button — it must not be removed.

## If a change seems necessary

1. Open a task / PR and explicitly ask the project owner: *"Can we modify the email verification flow?"*
2. Re-run the QA checklist in `docs/qa/PRODUCT-QA-TEST-PLAN.md` — Blocks B1 and B2 — before merging.
3. Update `docs/qa/PRODUCT-QA-TEST-PLAN.md` if expected behavior changes.
